Content:
Brezje pri Loah is a settlement in the Municipality of Slovenske Konjice in eastern Slovenia. It lies on the edge of the valley of the Dravinja River to the east of Slovenske Konjice and to the north of Loe. The area is part of the traditional Lower Styria region. The municipality is included in the Savinja statistical region.[2] The name of the settlement was changed from Breze to Brezje pri Loah in 1953.[3] Administrative centre: Slovenske Konjice
